query.result:
7 A gentle breeze, without 8 having any change in itself, struck my forehead 9 no more sharply than a soft wind;
10 because of which the leaves, trembling, promptly 11 all bent towards the part 12 where the holy mountain casts its first shadow;
13 not however from their upright being parted 14 so much that the little birds in the treetops 15 stopped practicing all their art;
16 but with full joy they welcomed the first hours, 17 singing, among the leaves, 18 which kept the bass to their melodies,
19 such as is gathered from branch to branch 20 through the pine forest on the shore of Chiassi, 21 when Aeolus unleashes the south-southeast wind.

